The Cauchy-Schwarz Inequality is a mathematical inequality relating the magnitudes of vectors in an inner product space. It is named after Augustin-Louis Cauchy and Hermann Schwarz.Initially, this inequality was proved in the 1850s.The product of the magnitudes of two vectors is greater than or equal to the magnitude of their dot product. This inequality is widely used in various fields, such as mathematics, physics, and engineering. It is also known as the 'dot-multiply inequality'.

